page.title: 16BUILDINGS
page.content: I live in a small row of terrace houses.There are four streets March street,Goosehill Rd, Ellinsterrace and woodhouse mount.The houses are private.They are all old .I live on Goosehill Rd it is a corner house .There is a small fish shop and a corner shop.Behind my house there is a big field.There is a park it has only got swings in.Up Ellins Terrace there are some gardens.There are some gardens.There is a pub near where I live,it is called the Hark To Mopsey, my friend Anna lives there.The buses come every quater of an hour to both Wakefield and Castleford. Most terrace housing can be found near the town shopping centre(grid square 3822).East of this area private residential properties have been built,these consist of detatched and semi-detatched houses.
